sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: AND gate structure for regulation of E.coli in CF mucus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device will have the cells live in the presence of LasL and Sialic acid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device, in the presence of HrpS and HrpR, will produce the regulator TetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device will detect the presence of LasL which is a signaling molecule used by P. aeruginosa. This is tied to make HrpR which is needed in the HrpL AND gate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This design will produce one of two necessary transcription factors for the HrpL AND gate. This will produce it in the presence of Sialic Acid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: we wanted a Negative Feed Back loop

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In the absence of tetR, this device will make granulysin and DNase1 which will kill the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: we needed to have a way to make sure both the membrane and genome of the cell was destroyed. These enzymes seemed like the best idea.
